- [ ] 2.2 Exercise 3:  Prove by induction that 1 + 5 + 9 + ... + (4n-3) = n(2n-1)
- [ ] Prove that for any positive integer number n, n^3 + 2n is divisible by 3			
- [ ] Prove that for n >= 1, 9^n âˆ’ 1 is divisible by 8 for all non-negative integers
		Hint: 4^(3+1) = 4 * 4^3
		Hint: If 9^n - 1 = 8m, then 9^n = 8m + 1 
    
1. 1 + 5 + 9 + ... + (4n-3) = n(2n-1)
   1 = 1(2(1)-1)
   1 = 1(2-1)
   1 = 1(1)
   1 = 1
   
   1 + 5 + 9 + ... + (4n-3) + (4(n+1)-3) = (n+1)(2(n+1)-1)
   n(2n-1) + (4n+4-3) = (n+1)(2n+2-1)
   2n^2-n + 4n+1 = 2n^2+2n-n+2n+2-1
   2n^2 + 3n + 1 = 2n^2 + 3n + 1
   
2. m = (n^3+2n)/3
   3m = n^3 + 2n
   3m = (n+1)^3 + 2(n+1)
   3m = (n+1)(n^2+2n+1) + 2n+2
   3m = n^3+n^2+2n^2+2n+n+1 + 2n+2
   3m = n^3 + 3n^2 + 3n + 2n + 3
   3m = 3m + 3n^2 + 3n + 3
   3m = 3(m + n^2 + n + 1)
   3m = 3m
   
3. m = (9^n-1)/8
   8m = 9^n - 1
   8m + 1 = 9^n
   8m + 1 = 9^(n+1)
   8m + 1 = 9^n * 9
   8m + 1 = (8m+1)*9
   8m + 1 = 72m + 9
   pos(m) + (pos) = (pos)m + (pos) => pos = pos
